member.name: T:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType
member.summary: Location types for a reverse geocoding request.
member.remarks: See Reverse Geocoding for more detail.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType.Unknown
member.summary: Indicates an unknown location type returned by the server.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType.Rooftop
member.summary: Restricts the results to addresses for which we have location information accurate down to street address precision.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType.RangeInterpolated
member.summary: Restricts the results to those that reflect an approximation (usually on a road) interpolated between two precise points (such as intersections). An interpolated range generally indicates that rooftop geocodes are unavailable for a street address.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType.GeometricCenter
member.summary: Restricts the results to geometric centers of a location such as a polyline (for example, a street) or polygon (region).

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.LocationType.Approximate
member.summary: Restricts the results to those that are characterized as approximate.

member.name: T:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.TrafficModel
member.summary: Specifies traffic prediction model when requesting future directions.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.TrafficModel.BestGuess
member.summary: Indicates that the returned 'duration_in_traffic' should be the best estimate of travel time given what is known about both historical traffic conditions and live traffic.
member.remarks: Live traffic becomes more important the closer the 'departure_time' is to now.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.TrafficModel.Optimistic
member.summary: Indicates that the returned 'duration_in_traffic' should be shorter than the actual travel time on most days, though occasional days with particularly good traffic conditions may be faster than this value.

member.name: F:Google.Maps.WebServices.Common.TrafficModel.Pessimistic
member.summary: Indicates that the returned 'duration_in_traffic' should be longer than the actual travel time on most days, though occasional days with particularly bad traffic conditions may exceed this value.

remarks.para: Additionally, you can request that the points be interpolated, resulting in a path that smoothly follows the geometry of the road.
